  "url": "https://www.tamilmirror.lk/\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd/\u0b89\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc8-\u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd-\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4-\u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd/175-302399",
  "time_ut": 1660574261,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "'\u0b89\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd'",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'We look forward to further strengthening the relationship'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "As India is celebrating the 75th anniversary of India's independence today, I extend my best wishes to our brothers and sisters in Sri Lanka. Meanwhile, it is a matter of great joy that Sri Lanka has also reached the 75th year of its independence.",
        "A series of events were held across Sri Lanka on this historic occasion, marking the 75th anniversary of India's independence (Asadika Amrit Mahotsav). The most important event of these celebrations can be mentioned the 75th Independence Day events jointly celebrated by India and Sri Lanka.",
        "Friends, India always has the people of Sri Lanka and their welfare in mind under the guidelines of Neighbor First Policy. As an indication of India's commitment to our Sri Lankans, an unprecedented amount of financial, economic and humanitarian assistance worth USD 4 billion has been provided this year. It is significant that India and the Indian people have come forward to address the various needs of the people of Sri Lanka quickly through our diversified assistance.",
        "Bilateral relations are emerging and developing in various new fields. During the visit of External Affairs Minister Dr. S. Jaishankar to Sri Lanka in March 2022, eight major agreements were signed between the two governments. The agreements range from Sri Lanka's unique digital identity system project to a US$15 million donation for the development of Buddhist communications, to defense and other issues. These are the inspirations of our relationship.",
        "India has been an active partner in driving Sri Lanka's economic recovery. Mutually beneficial Indian investments in various sectors such as ports, renewable energy, infrastructure etc. are significant factors in economic growth and employment growth.",
        "Cultural links between the two countries, common traditions and people-to-people bonds are the hallmarks of India-Sri Lanka relations. As we today move rapidly along the path created by our forefathers, we look forward to further strengthening this ancient bond for future generations.",
        "Once again I convey my best wishes to all the Indians in Sri Lanka and Sri Lankan brothers and sisters."
      ],
